Package: RfmallocStatgen
Title: Statistical Genetics on Rfmalloc Genotype Tensors
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Sounkou Mahamane", family = "Toure", email = "sounkoutoure@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person(given = "Zilong", family = "Li", role = "cph", comment = "PCAone randomized-SVD core")
    )
Description: Runs genome-scale statistical genetics methods over Rfmalloc's
    file-backed, compressed genotype tensors ('bed' at 2 bits per genotype,
    'dosage' at 1 byte per genotype), closing over the analysis stack
    popularized by 'bigsnpr' and 'bigstatsr' on denser storage with native
    readers, and adding haplotype methods that a genotype-only stack cannot
    express. Methods are implemented from published algorithms and validated
    against 'bigsnpr' and 'bigstatsr' as numerical oracles. The exception is
    the randomized-SVD workhorse, which is pinned from GPL-3 'PCAone' (Li
    2023) with a deterministic dependency trim and R-console adaptation.
    The current surface includes streamed univariate regression and principal
    components, banded linkage disequilibrium, LDpred2, and an all-pairs
    colocalisation expressed as a single matrix multiply over any registered
    compute backend.
